@noviceartisan I am not able to advise on this, but am aware of something you might consider:
Once you have a patent you need to be in a position to defend it. So, if a large and rich firm or individual wishes to steal your patent (which is now public knowledge) you need to be able to afford a protected law-suit. For some people, it is better to keep the invention secret and develop it and bring it to market themselves. 
Just something to consider.
